Brunsbüttel Nuclear Power Plant.label: Brunsbüttel Nuclear Power Plant
Brunsbüttel Nuclear Power Plant.description: Brunsbüttel Nuclear Power Plant is a nuclear power plant in Brunsbüttel near Hamburg, Germany. It is owned 67% by Vattenfall and 33% by E.ON. It started operation in 1976 and has a gross power production of 806 MW. Wikipedia

Buksefjord hydroelectric power plant.label: Buksefjord hydroelectric power plant
Buksefjord hydroelectric power plant.description: The Buksefjord hydroelectric power plant is the first and largest hydroelectric power plant in Greenland. It was built by Nuuk-Kraft and it is operated by Nukissiorfiit - Greenland's national energy company. Wikipedia

Buschhaus Power Station.label: Buschhaus Power Station
Buschhaus Power Station.description: Buschhaus Power Station is a lignite-fired power station near Helmstedt in Lower Saxony, Germany. It is operated by Helmstedter Revier GmbH, a subsidiary company of MIBRAG. Until end of 2013, the power station was owned by E.ON. Wikipedia

Goldisthal Pumped Storage Station.label: Goldisthal Pumped Storage Station
Goldisthal Pumped Storage Station.description: The Goldisthal Pumped Storage Station is a pumped-storage power station in the Thüringer Mountains at the upper run of the river Schwarza in Goldisthal, Germany. It was constructed between 1997 and 2004. Wikipedia

Greifswald Nuclear Power Plant.label: Greifswald Nuclear Power Plant
Greifswald Nuclear Power Plant.description: Greifswald nuclear power station, also known as Lubmin nuclear power station, was the largest nuclear power station in East Germany before closure shortly after the German reunification. Wikipedia

Grohnde Nuclear Power Plant.label: Grohnde Nuclear Power Plant
Grohnde Nuclear Power Plant.description: The Grohnde Nuclear Power Plant is located in Hamelin-Pyrmont in Lower Saxony. It has one reactor that uses 193 fuel assemblies and utilizes both enriched uranium and MOX fuel. Wikipedia

Heysham nuclear power station.label: Heysham 1 Nuclear Power Station
Heysham nuclear power station.description: Heysham Power Station is a nuclear power station located in Heysham, Lancashire, England, operated by EDF Energy. Wikipedia

Irsching Power Station.label: Irsching Power Station
Irsching Power Station.description: Irsching Power Station is close to the city of Vohburg, Germany and is operated as a so-called peak load power station. Wikipedia

Hoover Dam.label: Hoover Dam
Hoover Dam.description: Hoover Dam, once known as Boulder Dam, is a concrete arch-gravity dam in the Black Canyon of the Colorado River, on the border between the US states of Arizona and Nevada. Wikipedia

Koeberg Nuclear Power Station.label: Koeberg Nuclear Power Station
Koeberg Nuclear Power Station.description: Koeberg nuclear power station is a nuclear power station in South Africa. It is currently the only commercial one in the country, and the sole commercial one in the entire African continent. Wikipedia

Loviisa Nuclear Power Plant.label: Loviisa Nuclear Power Plant
Loviisa Nuclear Power Plant.description: Loviisa Nuclear Power Plant, is a nuclear power plant located close to the Finnish city of Loviisa. It houses two Soviet-designed VVER-440/213 PWR reactors, each with a capacity of 510 MW. Wikipedia

Markersbach Pumped Storage Power Plant.label: Markersbach Pumped Storage Power Plant
Markersbach Pumped Storage Power Plant.description: The Markersbach Pumped Storage Power Plant is a hydroelectric power station utilizing pumped-storage technology in Markersbach, Germany. Wikipedia

Navajo Generating Station.label: Navajo Generating Station
Navajo Generating Station.description: Navajo Generating Station is a 2250 megawatt coal-fired powerplant located on the Navajo Indian Reservation, near Page, Arizona, United States. This plant provides electrical power to customers in Arizona, Nevada, and California. Wikipedia

Orot Rabin.label: Orot Rabin
Orot Rabin.description: Orot Rabin is a coal-fired power station situated on the Mediterranean coast in Hadera, Israel. It is owned and operated by Israel Electric Corporation. Wikipedia

Peñascal Wind Power Project.label: Peñascal Wind Power Project
Peñascal Wind Power Project.description:
The 404 megawatt Peñascal Wind Farm is located in Kenedy County, Texas and was completed in April 2010 by Iberdrola.
The wind farm has 168 Mitsubishi MHI 92 wind turbines, each with a capacity of 2.4 MW. Wikipedia

Rutenberg Power Station.label: Rutenberg Power Station
Rutenberg Power Station.description: Rutenberg Power Station is a coal-powered power plant situated on the Mediterranean coast in Ashkelon, Israel. Wikipedia

Schwarze Pumpe power station.label: Schwarze Pumpe power station
Schwarze Pumpe power station.description: Schwarze Pumpe power station is a modern lignite-fired power station in the "Schwarze Pumpe" district in Spremberg, Germany consisting of 2 x 800 megawatts units. It came into service in 1997-98 and was built by Siemens. Wikipedia
Schwarze Pumpe power station.Address: An der Alten Ziegelei 1, 03130 Spremberg, Germany

Stade Nuclear Power Plant.label: Stade Nuclear Power Plant
Stade Nuclear Power Plant.description: The Nuclear power station Stade operated from 1972 to 2003 in Bassenfleth close to the Schwinge-river mouth into the Elbe river. Wikipedia

Unterweser Nuclear Power Plant.label: Unterweser Nuclear Power Plant
Unterweser Nuclear Power Plant.description:
The nuclear power station Unterweser is a nuclear power plant in Kleinensiel, close to Nordenham.
When it first started up, it was the largest nuclear reactor in the world. It has 193 fuel assemblies. Wikipedia

Stendal Nuclear Power Plant.label: Stendal Nuclear Power Plant
Stendal Nuclear Power Plant.description: The Stendal Nuclear Power Station in East Germany, was to be the largest nuclear power station in Germany. After German reunification, and due to concerns about the Soviet design, construction was stopped and the power station was never completed. Wikipedia

Temelín Nuclear Power Station.label: Temelín Nuclear Power Station
Temelín Nuclear Power Station.description: Temelín Nuclear Power Station is located near Temelín, a small village in the Czech Republic. Temelín NPP is owned by ČEZ Group, which employs 1000 workers at this site. The adjacent castle Vysoký Hrádek serves as an information centre. Wikipedia

Walchensee Hydroelectric Power Station.label: Walchensee Hydroelectric Power Station
Walchensee Hydroelectric Power Station.description: The Walchensee Power Plant is a hydroelectric power station in Bavaria. With an installed output of 124 MW it is one the largest of its kind in Germany. It is south of Kochel, about 14 kilometres from the village of Walchensee. Wikipedia

Atlantic Array.label: Atlantic Array
Atlantic Array.description: Atlantic Array was a proposed offshore wind farm in the Bristol Channel, off the coast of North Devon and South Wales, United Kingdom. It is a development by RWE Npower Renewables. Wikipedia

Cofrentes Nuclear Power Plant.label: Cofrentes Nuclear Power Plant
Cofrentes Nuclear Power Plant.description: Cofrentes Nuclear Power Plant is a BWR-type nuclear power station located about 2 kilometres southeast of Cofrentes, Spain. Cofrentes NPP entered service on October 14, 1984, with an installed power capacity of 992 MWe. Wikipedia

José Cabrera Nuclear Power Station.label: José Cabrera Nuclear Power Station
José Cabrera Nuclear Power Station.description:
The José Cabrera Nuclear Power Station is a nuclear power station in Almonacid de Zorita, 70 kilometres east of Madrid, Spain.
The power plant consists of a single PWR of 160 MWe. It was operated by Unión Fenosa. Wikipedia

Alma Generating Station.label: Alma Generating Station
Alma Generating Station.description: Alma Station is a base load, coal fired, electrical power station located in Alma, Wisconsin in Buffalo County. Owned by Dairyland Power Cooperative, the Alma Station and John P. Madgett Station are part of its Alma site. Wikipedia

Blackhawk Generating Station.label: Blackhawk Generating Station
Blackhawk Generating Station.description: Blackhawk Generating Station is a natural gas fired, electrical power station located in Beloit, Wisconsin in Rock County. Primarily used for summer power peaking. Wikipedia

Columbia Energy Center.label: Columbia Energy Center
Columbia Energy Center.description: Columbia Energy Center is a base load, sub-bituminous coal-fired, electrical power station located in the town of Dekorra, Wisconsin, south of Portage in Columbia County. Wikipedia

Edgewater Generating Station.label: Edgewater Generating Station
Edgewater Generating Station.description: Edgewater Generating Station is a base load, coal fired, electrical power station located in the city of Sheboygan in Sheboygan County, Wisconsin. Wikipedia

Concord Generating Station.label: Concord Generating Station
Concord Generating Station.description: Concord Generating Station is a natural gas fired, electrical peaking power plant located in the town of Watertown in Jefferson County, Wisconsin. It is a four unit natural gas or #2 fuel oil combustion turbine facility. Wikipedia

Fisk Generating Station.label: Fisk Generating Station
Fisk Generating Station.description: The Fisk Generating Station, also known as Fisk Street Generating Station or Fisk Station is a medium-size, coal-fired electric generating station located at 1111 West Cermak Road in the Pilsen neighborhood of Chicago, Illinois. Wikipedia

Blount Generating Station.label: Blount Generating Station
Blount Generating Station.description: Blount Generating Station, also known as Blount Street Generating Station is a natural gas-fired, electrical power station located in the city of Madison, Wisconsin, in Dane County. Wikipedia

Genoa Generating Station.label: Genoa Generating Station
Genoa Generating Station.description: Genoa Generating Station is a base load, coal fired, electrical power station located south of Genoa, Wisconsin in Vernon County. Wikipedia

French Island Generating Plant.label: French Island Generating Plant
French Island Generating Plant.description: French Island Generating Plant is a waste fired electrical power station located on French Island in La Crosse, Wisconsin. Unit 1 and 2 are boiler / steam turbine units originally constructed in the 1940s operating on coal. Wikipedia

Gibson Generating Station.label: Gibson Generating Station
Gibson Generating Station.description: The Gibson Generating Station is a coal-burning power plant located at the northern end of northern Montgomery Township, Gibson County, Indiana, United States. Wikipedia

Harllee Branch Power Plant.label: Harllee Branch Power Plant
Harllee Branch Power Plant.description: Plant Harllee Branch is a coal-fired power station located in southeastern Putnam County, just southeast of Eatonton, Georgia, USA. It is located about halfway between Eatonton and Milledgeville, to the southeast. Wikipedia

Goose Creek Energy Center.label: Goose Creek Energy Center
Goose Creek Energy Center.description: Goose Creek Energy Center is a 450 megawatt natural gas fired power station located in Goose Creek township, Piatt County, Illinois between Lodge, Illinois and De Land, Illinois. Wikipedia

Marshall Steam Station.label: Marshall Steam Station
Marshall Steam Station.description: Marshall Steam Station is a coal power plant located at 35°35′51″N 80°57′53″W﻿ / ﻿35.59750°N 80.96472°W in Terrell, Catawba County, North Carolina, United States and owned by Duke Energy. Wikipedia

Nelson Dewey Generating Station.label: Nelson Dewey Generating Station
Nelson Dewey Generating Station.description: Nelson Dewey Generating Station is a base load, coal fired, electrical power station located in Cassville, Wisconsin in Grant County. The station is owned by Wisconsin Power and Light Company, an Alliant Energy company. Wikipedia

Mangahao Power Station.label: Mangahao Power Station
Mangahao Power Station.description: Mangahao Power Station is a hydroelectric power station near the town of Shannon, New Zealand. After being delayed by war, access roading and foundation testing was started by late 1919 and the station opened in November 1924. Wikipedia

Huntly Power Station.label: Huntly Power Station
Huntly Power Station.description: The Huntly Power Station is the largest thermal power station in New Zealand and is located in the town of Huntly in the Waikato. It is operated by Genesis Energy Limited, a state-owned enterprise, and supplies around 17% of the country's power. Wikipedia

Northport Power Station.label: Northport Power Station
Northport Power Station.description: The Northport Power Station is a natural gas and conventional oil electric power generating station located on the north shore of Long Island, at Waterside Avenue & Eatons Neck Road in Northport, New York. Wikipedia

Paris Generating Station.label: Paris Generating Station
Paris Generating Station.description: Paris Generating Station is a natural gas fired, electrical peaking power plant located in the town of Paris in Kenosha County, south east of Union Grove, Wisconsin. Wikipedia

Oak Creek Power Plant.label: Oak Creek Power Plant
Oak Creek Power Plant.description: Oak Creek Power Plant, also known as South Oak Creek, is a base load, coal- and natural gas-fired, electrical power station located on Lake Michigan in Oak Creek, Wisconsin. Wikipedia

Ohaaki Power Station.label: Ohaaki Power Station
Ohaaki Power Station.description: The Ohaaki Power Station is a geothermal power station owned and operated by Contact Energy. A distinctive feature of this power station is the 105 m high natural draft cooling tower, the only one of its kind in New Zealand. Wikipedia

Mount Storm Power Station.label: Mount Storm Power Station
Mount Storm Power Station.description: The Mount Storm Power Station, located on the west bank of Mount Storm Lake 2 miles from Bismarck, West Virginia, is a coal-fired power station owned by Dominion Resources. It is the largest power plant that Dominion operates. Wikipedia

Pleasant Prairie Power Plant.label: Pleasant Prairie Power Plant
Pleasant Prairie Power Plant.description: Pleasant Prairie Power Plant is a base load, coal fired, electrical power station located in Pleasant Prairie, Wisconsin in Kenosha County. Wikipedia

Riverside Energy Center.label: Riverside Energy Center
Riverside Energy Center.description: Riverside Energy Center is an electrical power station located north of Beloit, Wisconsin in the town of Beloit at 1401 W B R Townline Road just west of the Rock River. The facility is owned and operated by Alliant Energy. Wikipedia

RockGen Energy Center.label: RockGen Energy Center
RockGen Energy Center.description: RockGen Energy Center is a 460 megawatt natural gas fired peaking power plant located near Rockdale, Wisconsin. According to Calpine, it was the largest peaking plant in Wisconsin at the time it was constructed. Wikipedia

Rock River Generating Station.label: Rock River Generating Station
Rock River Generating Station.description: Rock River Generating Station is an electrical power station located north of Beloit, Wisconsin in the town of Beloit at 827 W. B. R. Townline Road on the west bank of the Rock River. Wikipedia

Valley Power Plant.label: Valley Power Plant
Valley Power Plant.description: Valley Power Plant is an intermediate load, coal fired, electrical power station located in Milwaukee, Wisconsin. The plant is a cogeneration facility supplying steam to 480 customers and 280 MW of electricity. Wikipedia

Vogtle Electric Generating Plant.label: Vogtle Electric Generating Plant
Vogtle Electric Generating Plant.description: The Alvin W. Vogtle Electric Generating Plant, also known as Plant Vogtle, is a 2-unit nuclear power plant located in Burke County, near Waynesboro, Georgia in the southeastern United States. Wikipedia

Leningrad Nuclear Power Plant.label: Leningrad Nuclear Power Plant
Leningrad Nuclear Power Plant.description: Leningrad Nuclear Power Plant is a nuclear power plant located in the town of Sosnovy Bor in Russia's Leningrad Oblast, on the southern shore of the Gulf of Finland, some 70 kilometres to the west of the city centre of Saint Petersburg. Wikipedia

Kashiwazaki-Kariwa Nuclear Power Plant.label: Kashiwazaki-Kariwa Nuclear Power Plant
Kashiwazaki-Kariwa Nuclear Power Plant.description: The Kashiwazaki-Kariwa Nuclear Power Plant is a large, modern nuclear power plant on a 4.2-square-kilometer site including land in the towns of Kashiwazaki and Kariwa in Niigata Prefecture, Japan on ... Wikipedia

Salvajina Dam.label: Salvajina Dam
Salvajina Dam.description: The Salvajina Dam and hydroelectric plant are located in the Cauca River, corregimiento Buenos Aires, municipality Suarez, department Cauca in the southwest of Colombia. Its reservoir has a length of 31 kilometres. Wikipedia

Clark Canyon Dam.label: Clark Canyon Dam
Clark Canyon Dam.description: Clark Canyon Dam is an earthfill dam located in Beaverhead County, Montana, about 20 miles south of the county seat of Dillon. The dam impounds the waters of the Beaverhead River, creating a body of water known as Clark Canyon Reservoir. Wikipedia

Arnedo Solar Plant.label: Arnedo Solar Plant
Arnedo Solar Plant.description: The Arnedo Solar Plant is a solar photovoltaic power plant located in Arnedo, La Rioja, Spain. The power system installations are supplied and the solar plant is operated by T-Solar. The plant was built by Isolux Corsán in 2008. Wikipedia

Jilintai I Dam.label: Jilintai I Dam
Jilintai I Dam.description: The Jilintai I Dam is a concrete-face rock-fill embankment dam on the Kashgar River, 29 km east of Nilka in Xinjiang, China. The dam was constructed between 2001 and 2005 for several purposes but mainly hydroelectric power generation. Wikipedia

Morrow Point Dam.label: Morrow Point Dam
Morrow Point Dam.description: Morrow Point Dam is a 468-foot-tall concrete double-arch dam on the Gunnison River located in Colorado, the first dam of its type built by the U.S. Bureau of Reclamation. Wikipedia

Malutang Dam.label: Malutang Dam
Malutang Dam.description: The Malutang Dam is a concrete-face rock-fill dam on the Panlong River in Malipo County, Yunnan Province, China. The primary purpose of the dam is hydroelectric power generation and the power plant was constructed in two stages. Wikipedia

Acton Lane Power Station.label: Acton Lane Power Station
Acton Lane Power Station.description: Acton Lane Power Station was a power station in west London. The station was located to the south of the Grand Union Canal and west of the Dudding Hill railway line. Wikipedia

Łaziska Power Station.label: Łaziska Power Station
Łaziska Power Station.description: Łaziska Power Station is a thermal power station in Łaziska Górne, Poland. The first Łaziska Power Station was inaugurated in 1917. In 1929, an 87.1 MW unit was inaugurated making it to the largest power station in Poland at those days. Wikipedia

Rheidol Power Station.label: Rheidol Power Station
Rheidol Power Station.description: Rheidol power station is a 56 MW hydroelectric scheme near Aberystwyth, Wales. It was built between 1957 and 1962 and was officially opened on 3 July 1964. Wikipedia

Arecleoch Wind Farm.label: Arecleoch Wind Farm
Arecleoch Wind Farm.description: Arecleoch Wind Farm is a 60 turbine wind farm in South Ayrshire, Scotland with a total capacity of 120 megawatts, enough to power over 67,000 homes. Construction started in 2009 and it was commissioned in June 2011. Wikipedia

Alta Wind Energy Center.label: Alta Wind Energy Center
Alta Wind Energy Center.description: The Alta Wind Energy Center is a wind farm located in Tehachapi Pass of the Tehachapi Mountains, in Kern County, California. As of 2013, it is the largest wind farm in the world, with a combined installed capacity of 1,320 MW. Wikipedia

Athlone Power Station.label: Athlone Power Station
Athlone Power Station.description:
Athlone Power Station was a coal-fired power station in Athlone, Cape Town, South Africa.
The power station was commissioned in 1962 with 6 turbines with a nominal capacity of 180 megawatts, and operated by the City of Cape Town. Wikipedia

Buseruka Power Station.label: Kabalega Hydroelectric Power Station
Buseruka Power Station.description: Kabalega Hydroelectric Power Station, also known as Kabalega Power Station is a 9.0 MW mini hydroelectric power project located across River Wambabya, in Buseruka Sub County, Hoima District, in Western Uganda. Wikipedia

Billingham Biomass Power Station.label: Billingham Biomass Power Station
Billingham Biomass Power Station.description: Billingham Biomass Power Station is a planned biomass power station, that is to be built on the River Tees at Billingham. It is to be built on the site of the former coal-fired North Tees Power Station. Wikipedia

Camden Power Station.label: Camden Power Station
Camden Power Station.description: Camden Power Station in Mpumalanga, South Africa, is a coal-fired power plant operated by Eskom. Wikipedia

Dhirubhai Ambani Solar Park.label: Dhirubhai Ambani Solar Park
Dhirubhai Ambani Solar Park.description: The Dhirubhai Ambani Solar Park at Dhursar village near Pokran in the Jaisalmer district of Rajasthan is one of a large number of solar parks expected to be built in a 35,000 km² area of the Thar Desert ... Wikipedia

Guru Nanak Dev Thermal Plant.label: Guru Nanak Dev Thermal Plant
Guru Nanak Dev Thermal Plant.description: The Guru Nanak Dev Thermal Plant at Bathinda is one of the three thermal power stations in Punjab. It is a medium-sized power station with four units that were begun to be built in early 1970s and completed in 1982. Wikipedia

Incheon Tidal Power Station.label: Incheon Tidal Power Station
Incheon Tidal Power Station.description: The Incheon Tidal Power Station is a large tidal power station currently under construction at the Incheon Bay, South Korea. Wikipedia

Kinyara Power Station.label: Kinyara Power Station
Kinyara Power Station.description: Kinyara Power Station is a 14.5MW bagasse-fired thermal power plant located in the town of Kinyara in Masindi District, in Western Uganda. Wikipedia

Hongsibao Solar Park.label: Hongsibao Solar Park
Hongsibao Solar Park.description: The Hongsibao Solar Park is a 50 MWp photovoltaic power station located in the Ningxia region, in China. Most of it uses fixed tilt arrays, but a 2 MW tracker section was completed in 2011. The first stage, 20 MWp, was completed in 2010. Wikipedia

Matimba Power Station.label: Matimba Power Station
Matimba Power Station.description: Matimba Power Station close to Ellisras, Limpopo Province, South Africa, is a coal-fired power plant operated by Eskom. Wikipedia

Lugazi Power Station.label: Lugazi Power Station
Lugazi Power Station.description: Lugazi Power Station is a 8.6MW bagasse-fired thermal power plant located in the town of Lugazi in Buikwe District, in Central Uganda. Wikipedia

Kepier power station.label: Kepier power station
Kepier power station.description: Kepier power station refers to a cancelled coal-fired power station on the River Wear at Kepier, 0.75 miles north east of Durham, County Durham, North East England. Wikipedia

Pates Hill Wind Farm.label: Pates Hill Wind Farm
Pates Hill Wind Farm.description: Pates Hill Wind Farm is located near the village of West Calder in West Lothian, Scotland. It consists of 7 Vestas V-80 wind turbines, measuring 107 metres to the blade tip. Wikipedia

Presenzano Hydroelectric Plant.label: Presenzano Hydroelectric Plant
Presenzano Hydroelectric Plant.description: The Presenzano Hydroelectric Plant, officially known as the Domenico Cimarosa Hydroelectric Plant, is located along the Volturno River in Presenzano, Province of Caserta, Italy. Wikipedia

Ruacana Dam.label: Ruacana Dam
Ruacana Dam.description: The Ruacana Power Station is a hydroelectric power plant of the Kunene River in Namibia, not distant from the Angola border. It has a power generating capacity of 240 MW enough to power over 162,000 homes Wikipedia

Roncovalgrande Hydroelectric Plant.label: Roncovalgrande Hydroelectric Plant
Roncovalgrande Hydroelectric Plant.description: The Roncovalgrande Hydroelectric Plant, also known as the Delio Hydroelectric Plant, is located 3 km north of Maccagno in the Province of Varese, Lombardy, Italy. Wikipedia

Reefton Power Station.label: Reefton Power Station
Reefton Power Station.description:
Reefton Power Station was the first power station to supply municipal electricity in the Southern Hemisphere.
It supplied electricity to the town of Reefton in New Zealand. Wikipedia

Rzeszów Power Station.label: Rzeszów Power Station
Rzeszów Power Station.description: Rzeszow Power Station is a coal-fired thermal power station in Rzeszów, Poland. At the first stage four units with a thermal capacity of 25 MWt each were built between 1976 and 1983. Wikipedia

Sere Wind Farm.label: Sere Wind Farm
Sere Wind Farm.description: Sere Wind Farm is a wind-farm in the Western Cape province of South Africa that, 100MW when completed, will be one of the largest wind-farms in Southern Africa. The project is estimated to cost R2.689 billion. Wikipedia

Selkirk Generating Station.label: Selkirk Generating Station
Selkirk Generating Station.description: Selkirk Generating Station is a natural gas-fired station owned by Manitoba Hydro. It is located just across the Red River from Selkirk, Manitoba, Canada, in the Rural Municipality of St. Clements. Wikipedia

Siah Bishe Pumped Storage Power Plant.label: Siah Bishe Pumped Storage Power Plant
Siah Bishe Pumped Storage Power Plant.description: The Siah Bisheh Pumped Storage Power Plant, also spelled Siyāhbisheh and Siah Bishe, is located in the Alborz Mountain range near the village of Siah Bisheh and 48 km south of Chalus in Mazandaran Province, Iran. Wikipedia
